            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I was a day student in this wonderful school back in 2005-06 whileI was in 6th standard. A key part in this school was that the faculty and management did subtly differentiate between the day students and boarding students, although they tried their best to hide their differentiation. The food quality back then was top notch, they made it a point that students have prayers before lunch. The sports activities, cultural activities were also very good.\nThe school did its part to ensure discipline in the students by the medium of strict teachers and management.\nStill very proud to be an alumnus of this school.",
